CASE: Smith v. Pacific Medical Center
MATTER TYPE: Motor Vehicle Accident (MVA) / Personal Injury
DATE RANGE: March 15, 2025 - May 10, 2025
TOTAL PAGES REVIEWED: 312

EXECUTIVE SUMMARY:
Client sustained a high-velocity rear-end collision on 03/15/2025. Initial ER findings were suggestive of strain, but persistent symptoms led to an MRI on 03/24/2025 which confirmed a C5-C6 disc herniation. Client has underwent conservative treatment including PT and injections, with surgical intervention (ACDF) recommended.

CHRONOLOGICAL TIMELINE:

DATE        | PROVIDER/FACILITY             | FINDINGS/TREATMENT
------------|-------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------
03/15/2025  | Pacific Medical Center - ER   | Chief complaint: Neck pain, headache, dizziness post-MVA. CT Cervical Spine: Negative for acute fracture. Dx: Cervical strain, concussion.
03/17/2025  | Dr. Sarah Chen, MD (PCP)      | Follow-up. Pt reports increased neck stiffness and radiating pain to left arm. MRI ordered. Prescribed PT 3x/week.
03/24/2025  | Pacific Imaging Center        | MRI CERVICAL SPINE: C5-C6 disc herniation with mild cord compression. No evidence of pre-existing degenerative changes at this level.
04/02/2025  | Dr. James Wilson (Neuro)      | Surgical Consult. Confirmed MRI findings. Recommended ACDF surgery.
04/10/2025  | Dr. Lisa Park (Pain Mgmt)     | Epidural Steroid Injection (ESI) at C5-C6. 40% relief reported.
05/01/2025  | Elite Physical Therapy        | Progress Note: Pt showing limited range of motion (ROM). Radiculopathy persists.
05/10/2025  | Dr. Sarah Chen, MD (PCP)      | Review of specialist findings. Referral for surgical clearance.

KEY EVIDENCE MARKERS:
- [03/24/2025] MRI confirms acute herniation at C5-C6.
- [04/02/2025] Surgical recommendation for ACDF establishes high case value.
- [05/01/2025] Documentation of failed conservative treatment (PT).

MEDICAL EXPENSES SUMMARY:
- Pacific Medical Center (ER): $4,250.00
